{
  "texts": [
    "Temperature plays a crucial role in shaping the electrical characteristics of solar cells, impacting both voltage and current output.",
    "Regarding voltage, the open-circuit voltage (Voc) diminishes with rising temperatures, influencing the maximum power point voltage (Vmpp).",
    "Vmpp, representing the voltage at which the solar cell achieves its peak power output, undergoes a decrease due to a shift in the voltage-temperature coefficient caused by temperature increases (An et al., 2019).",
    "In terms of current output, solar cells exhibit variations with changes in temperature.",
    "Elevated temperatures generally result in an increase in the short-circuit current (Isc), signifying the maximum current output under shortcircuit conditions."
  ]
}